WHY HAWAII'S CLIMATE DEMANDS PROFESSIONAL SERVICE

Oahu's high humidity and constant exposure to saline trade winds create a "perfect storm" for window A/C units. Unlike drier climates, Honolulu's air causes rapid condensation buildup within the internal casing of window units, which often goes unnoticed behind the front grill.

This moisture, combined with indoor dust, creates a fertile breeding ground for toxic mold (Aspergillus) and bacteria. Without regular professional sanitization, your window unit becomes a distribution system for allergens, causing "Sick Building Syndrome" symptoms like headaches, fatigue, and respiratory distress.

Furthermore, salt-air corrosion eats away at sensitive aluminum fins and copper tubing. Our deep cleaning process includes a specialized Corrosion Inhibitor Treatment that neutralizes salt deposits, potentially extending your unit's lifespan by 3-5 years.

FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS

How often should I have my window A/C professionally cleaned in Oahu?

Due to our high humidity and salt-air concentration, we recommend a deep clinical sanitization every 6-12 months for primary living spaces to prevent mold buildup and corrosion.

Does dirty window A/C impact electricity bills?

Yes. Clogged coils force the compressor to work 30-50% harder to achieve the same cooling effect, leading to significantly higher MECO/HECO bills and premature motor failure.

Can I just use a spray bottle from the hardware store?

Hardware store sprays only treat the surface. Our process involves full teardown and internal decontamination of the blower wheel and drain pan where 90% of mold actually resides.
